history.content: As far as I am aware, your waitlist position for the class does not matter - only the waitlist position for the lab. So if you have enrolled in a lab section that is open, you should be enrolled automatically sometime soon, and if you are on waitlist for the lab, you will still be waitlisted, but what would really matter would be the waitlist position of the lab, so you should be better off either way!

The student's response above is correct. Minor correction is that if you're waitlisted overall, you can't be enrolled in a lab at the same time; it's an all or nothing thing. 

The advice in bold above was to give students tips for better waitlist positions. The adjustment period begins next week and all unused reserved seats will be released at that time, so you want to be in a good position for that.

Please see the update after the one you highlighted indicating those labs have been closed at this time.

I enrolled in EE16A during my Phase I registration, and I was in waitlist position number 66 today. Right before my Phase II enrollment time, I saw that more lab sections were open so I decided to follow the advice from the pinned Piazza post, as seen below:

"Update #2, 7/23/18: EE16A has been expanded to 954 total seats. At this time, the extra seats are all being added to the EECS and LSCS senior category. Small new lab sections were created. Waitlisted students whose categories of seats are full may want to increase their chances by dropping themselves from the class in order to add one of the new lab sections; you are not able to switch secondary sections while waitlisted. We may be able to add up to 100 additional seats, but need to wait until the end of Phase II to see how many more seats we are able to add and which categories of students the seats will go to. I'll update again when I have more information."

I am a CoE undergrad and my category was full, so I figured the advice applied to me. I dropped the class and re-enrolled in it because I thought more spaces had opened up, but when I re-enrolled I was simply waitlisted at position 227. I was wondering if there is anything I can do to undo this since I lost my earlier waitlist position, and I was confused by the advice given in the Piazza post.
